        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 6:10PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 609 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Garden Valley, or 7
miles north of Oglethorpe. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Whitewater State Park, Garden Valley, Winchester, and Marshallville.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
